.TH "cpucycles-open" "1" "" "" ""
.hy
.SS NAME
.PP
cpucycles-open - open up cycle counting
.SS SYNOPSIS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
cpucycles-open
\f[R]
.fi
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[V]cpucycles-open\f[R] tries to change some aspects of OS
configuration to open up higher-quality cycle counters for
\f[V]cpucycles\f[R].
.PP
Some system administrators may wish to configure
\f[V]cpucycles-open\f[R] to be run on each boot.
However, what \f[V]cpucycles\f[R] does is contrary to some security
policies.
.PP
\f[V]cpucycles-open\f[R] often improves cycle counting, but does not
guarantee success.
.SS SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]cpucycles\f[R](3)
